<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,152,700]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,405,375,401]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Elevation range:</emphasis>
This is typically a high elevation species ranging from 
<quantity box="[1071,1237,376,402]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.620012" metricValueMax="1.8288" metricValueMin="1.411224" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="ft" value="5315.0" valueMax="6000.0" valueMin="4630.0">4630–6000 ft.</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[1254,1421,376,402]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6199999999999999" metricValueMax="1.829" metricValueMin="1.411" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="m" value="1620.0" valueMax="1829.0" valueMin="1411.0">1411–1829 m</quantity>
), but there is one record from 
<quantity box="[484,576,413,439]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8768" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="ft" value="1600.0">1600 ft.</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[591,667,413,439]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.11" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="m" value="411.0">411 m</quantity>
) along the Foothills Parkway.
</paragraph>
